Data loading and cleaning

Download dataset, convert to proper format. Dataset link: https://zenodo.org/records/4656049

# Replace 'your_file_path.tsf' with the actual path to your TSF file
file_path <- 'data/us_births_dataset.tsf'
# Read the lines starting from the line after '@data'
raw_data <- read.table(file_path, header = TRUE, sep = ',', stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
# Extract the date from the seventh row and replace the row value
first_date_value <- str_match(raw_data[7, 1], "^T\\d+:(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}) \\d{2}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}:\\d+")[, 2]
raw_data[7, 1] <- as.numeric(str_match(raw_data[7, 1], "\\d+$")[, 1])
# Drop the first 6 rows
raw_data <- raw_data[-(1:6), ]
# Create a tibble with the required columns
birth_data <- as_tibble(raw_data, rownames='date')
# Rename the 'value' column to 'num_births'
birth_data <- rename(birth_data, num_births = value)
# Create a 'Date' column starting from the first date
birth_data$date <- seq(as.Date(first_date_value), by = '1 day', length.out = nrow(birth_data))
birth_data <- birth_data %>%
  mutate(num_births = as.integer(num_births))
# Print the modified tibble
print(birth_data)

Train and validation data

Set up train/validation partition. Validation data is 1987 and train is 1988

df_train = filter(birth_data, date < '1988-01-01')
df_val = filter(birth_data, date >= '1988-01-01' & date <= '1988-12-31')

# Test for stationarity

Low p-value means TS is stationary

adf_result <- adf.test(df_train$num_births)
## Warning in adf.test(df_train$num_births): p-value smaller than printed p-value
kpss_result <- kpss.test(df_train$num_births)
## Warning in kpss.test(df_train$num_births): p-value smaller than printed p-value
print(paste("ADF p-value:", adf_result$p.value))
## [1] "ADF p-value: 0.01"
print(paste("KPSS p-value:", kpss_result$p.value))
## [1] "KPSS p-value: 0.01"

Both test suggest that series is stationary

Chose values for p, q in ARIMA(p, d, q)

Measuring results

MAPE Create reusable function to calculate MAPE

evaluate_mape <- function(actual_values, predicted_values) {
  absolute_percentage_errors <- abs((actual_values - predicted_values) / actual_values) * 100
  mape <- mean(absolute_percentage_errors, na.rm = TRUE)
  return(mape)
}

Train MA model

ma_model <- Arima(df_train$num_births, order = c(0, 0, 7), method = "ML")

#Train SARIMA and account for yearly seasonality

# Fit the SARIMA model
sarima_model <- Arima(df_train$num_births, order = c(7, 1, 7), seasonal = list(order = c(7, 1, 3), 365), 
                      method = "ML")
forecast_result <- forecast(sarima_model, h = 366)
actual_values <- df_val$num_births
predicted_values <- forecast_result$mean
mape <- evaluate_mape(actual_values, predicted_values)
print(paste("MAPE:", mape))
## [1] "MAPE: 4.79806490139405"

Monthly of data - graph for demonstration

# Create a new column for the year and month
df_train$year_month <- format(df_train$date, "%Y-%m")
df_train$year_month <- as.Date(paste0(df_train$year_month, "-01"))
# Calculate the monthly number of births
monthly_data <- df_train %>%
  group_by(year_month) %>%
  summarize(avg_births = mean(as.numeric(num_births)))


# Filter only data from 1980 and onwards
filtered_data <- filter(monthly_data, year(year_month) >= 1980)

# Plot monthly values for the filtered period
ggplot(filtered_data, aes(x = year_month, y = avg_births)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line() +
  labs(title = "Monthly Number of Births (1980 and onwards)",
       x = "Year-Month",
       y = "Avg Number of Births")
